132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 166
H.P. 99 House of Representatives, January 14, 2025
An Act to Prohibit the Sale of Tobacco Products in Pharmacies and
Retail Establishments Containing Pharmacies
Reference to the Committee on Health and Human Services suggested and ordered printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative MOONEN of Portland.
Cosponsored by Senator INGWERSEN of York and
Representatives: DEBRITO of Waterville, MCCABE of Lewiston, MEYER of Eliot,
SHAGOURY of Hallowell, ZAGER of Portland, Senator: GUERIN of Penobscot.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 22 MRSA ยง1551, sub-ยง6 is enacted to read:
3 6. Pharmacy. "Pharmacy" means a retail pharmacy as defined in Title 24-A, section
4 4347, subsection 19.
5 Sec. 2. 22 MRSA ยง1551-A, sub-ยง6 is enacted to read:
6 6. Pharmacies and retail establishments with a pharmacy ineligible for retail
7 tobacco license; civil penalty; transfer of funds. This subsection governs pharmacies
8 and retail establishments containing a pharmacy.
9 A. A pharmacy is ineligible for a retail tobacco license. A pharmacy that engages in
10 retail sales, including retail sales through vending machines or in free distribution of
11 tobacco products, and sells, keeps for sale or gives away in the course of trade any
12 tobacco products to anyone commits a civil violation for which a fine of not more than
13 $2,000 may be adjudged. Each day a pharmacy is in violation of this paragraph
14 constitutes a separate offense.
15 B. A retail establishment containing a pharmacy is ineligible for a retail tobacco
16 license. A retail establishment containing a pharmacy that engages in retail sales,
17 including retail sales through vending machines or in free distribution of tobacco
18 products, and sells, keeps for sale or gives away in the course of trade any tobacco
19 products to anyone commits a civil violation for which a fine of not more than $2,000
20 may be adjudged. Each day a retail establishment containing a pharmacy is in violation
21 of this paragraph constitutes a separate offense.
22 Sec. 3. Effective date. This Act takes effect January 1, 2026.
23 SUMMARY
2244 This bill provides that pharmacies and retail establishments containing a pharmacy are
2255 ineligible for a retail tobacco license and provides that a pharmacy or retail establishment
2266 containing a pharmacy that engages in retail sales of tobacco products commits a civil
2277 violation.
